#: of numpy.nanpercentile:82
msgid ""
"If `q` is a single percentile and `axis=None`, then the result is a scalar. "
"If multiple percentiles are given, first axis of the result corresponds to "
"the percentiles. The other axes are the axes that remain after the reduction "
"of `a`. If the input contains integers or floats smaller than ``float64``, "
"the output data-type is ``float64``. Otherwise, the output data-type is the "
"same as that of the input. If `out` is specified, that array is returned "
"instead."
